DeoDap Care — Final Customer-Care Mail Flow
Two-system design: Mail Engine (System 1) + Care Panel (System 2)
Final version — consolidates the voice notes, the Ticket Engine ASCII flow, and the Mail Integration plan  |  v2.0 FINAL  |  June 2026
1. The two systems & the golden rule
	System 1 — Mail Engine	System 2 — Care Panel (care.deodap.in)
Owns	The mailbox (deodap.4300@gmail.com). Every inbound mail and every outbound mail goes through it. Holds the ignore list, AI classification, auto-replies, evidence loops and mail-side states.	The tickets. Ticket IDs (TKT-2026-NNNNNN), comments, media storage, agent assignment, the agent pipeline and the dashboard.
Never does	Never stores ticket state of record — it only mirrors the TKT id it received.	Never reads or sends email directly. It only receives API calls from the Mail Engine (and can call back via webhook).
Talks via	Calls 3 Care Panel APIs: open-ticket check, create ticket, add comment/media.	Returns ticket id + tracking link; optionally fires a webhook on agent reply / status change.
Golden rule: a ticket exists ONLY when a human must act. Everything the Mail Engine can answer and close via API (Shopify + ship.deodap.com) stays as auto_resolved on the mail side — no ticket, no care-panel noise. This keeps the panel queue 100% actionable.
2. End-to-end flow — 12 steps
1.	Fetch: new mail arrives at deodap.4300@gmail.com → pulled via Gmail push (fallback: IMAP UID watermark polling).
2.	Dedup: Message-ID already seen? → skip silently.
3.	Ignore gate: spam / marketing / newsletter / sender on the manual block list → label, log, STOP. No reply, no ticket. (Only complaints and customer enquiries pass — everything else is excluded.)
4.	Assign brand + mailbox: decide which store/brand the mail belongs to (alias, order prefix, content).
5.	Extract: email, phone, order#, AWB (AI path), description, images, videos — from body, subject and attachments.
6.	Self-lookup: before asking the customer anything, try the two APIs — Shopify (order/customer) and ship.deodap.com (AWB/courier). The sender email itself is a search key. If still nothing → auto-mail M1 asking for registered order# / email / mobile / AWB or any other detail registered with the order → state awaiting_evidence.
7.	AI classify: Groq (fallback: Gemini) → category + sub-topic + confidence, matched against the static query list from the playbook document.
8.	Confidence gate: confidence < 0.75 → no automation. Draft a reply, assign to agent, state awaiting_agent.
9.	Action router: Route A auto-answer & close (no ticket) · Route B evidence loop then ticket · Route C direct ticket · Route D sensitive → human. (Section 4.)
10.	Evidence loop (Route B): video/photo first if the category demands it; then the mandatory fields — order# and phone are asked TOGETHER in one mail if missing. Evidence complete = order# + phone + description (+ media where required).
11.	Existing-ticket check: query Care Panel open-tickets for the same verified customer + same order. Same issue id already open → append comment + media, reply with the EXISTING ticket number and tracking link (no new ticket). Different issue on the same order → proceed as new (e.g. #100 Delayed → #101 Wrong Item).
12.	Create & confirm: create the Care Panel ticket (store-json, phone-keyed) → upload media (sha256-deduped, webp→png) → generate tracking link care.deodap.in/t?id=hash → send confirmation mail with TKT id + link → state awaiting_agent.
3. Gate details (IF / THEN / Action)
3a. Ignore gate & dedup
IF (condition)	THEN	Action
Message-ID already processed	Skip silently.	—
AI says marketing / newsletter / promotional	Mark as Marketing, exclude. No action of any kind beyond labelling + log.	ignored
Sender is on the manual ignore list (admin-entered mail IDs)	Blocked + logged. Can never become a ticket — this is how any customer/sender can be blocked.	ignored
Cannot deduce anything but clearly not a customer complaint/enquiry	Mark for the daily review label; no auto-reply.	ignored (review)
Real customer complaint / enquiry	Continue to extraction.	new

3b. Identity & contact resolution
IF (condition)	THEN	Action
Order# or AWB extracted	Shopify order lookup (order#) / ship.deodap.com lookup (AWB) → load order, customer, courier status.	Continue
No order#/AWB, but phone or sender email matches a Shopify customer	Pull recent orders; exactly 1 recent → auto-select; 2+ → ask which one.	Continue / M1
Nothing extractable AND no API match on any contact	Auto-mail M1: please share registered order number, email ID, mobile, AWB number, or any other detail registered with the order.	awaiting_evidence
Reply arrives on a waiting thread	Re-extract, merge with the same case, resume where it stopped.	Loop
4. Action router — four routes
Route	Categories (static list)	What happens	Ticket?
A — Auto-answer & close	FAQ, policy, store info, order status / EDD / tracking, serviceability, invoice copy — anything fully answerable from the document + APIs	Mail Engine pulls live data (Shopify + Ship), sends the answer, closes.	NO ticket — auto_resolved
B — Evidence → ticket	Defective / damaged, missing item, wrong item, return, refund claims	Video/photo request first (waiting_for_video) → then order# + phone together in ONE mail if missing → evidence complete → Section 5.	YES, after evidence complete
C — Direct ticket	Delay / EDD breach, expedite request, address change after dispatch, RTO, POD request	Mandatory fields check (order# + phone + description) → Section 5. No media needed.	YES
D — Human first	Payment disputes, fraud, legal / consumer-court threat, abusive tone, anything sensitive or live-data sensitive, confidence < 0.75	Draft reply prepared, assigned to agent; high-priority flag where needed.	Agent decides (awaiting_agent / escalated)
Rule: Routes B and C converge at EVIDENCE COMPLETE — both then pass the existing-ticket check before anything is created.
5. Existing-ticket check → create → confirm
IF (condition)	THEN	Customer gets
Open ticket exists for same customer + same order + SAME issue id (sub-topic mapped to Care Panel issue id)	Do NOT create a new ticket. /t/add_comment appends the new mail + media to the existing ticket (Ticket Updated).	Mail M6 — existing TKT number + tracking link: “your ticket is already open; updates will come on this number.”
Open ticket exists for same customer + same order but DIFFERENT issue	Continue as new — one issue = one ticket (e.g. #100 Delayed and #101 Wrong Item can both be open on one order).	Mail M5 — new TKT number + link
No open ticket	Create Care Panel ticket (store-json, phone-keyed) → upload media → generate tracking link.	Mail M5 — new TKT number + link

6. Care Panel API contract (the only bridge between the systems)
Call	When	Payload	Returns
GET open-tickets	Before every ticket creation	Verified email + phone, order#, issue id	List of open tickets (id, issue, status)
POST create-ticket	Evidence complete + no same-issue open ticket	store-json: brand, customer (phone-keyed), order#, category/sub-topic → issue id, description	TKT-2026-NNNNNN
POST /t/add_comment	Same-issue ticket exists, or extra info arrives later on any ticket	Comment text + media files (sha256-deduped; webp converted to png)	OK
Webhook (recommended)	Agent replies / status changes in the panel	TKT id, new status, agent message	Mail Engine sends the update mail to the customer — so the panel still never touches the mailbox
Media rules: every attachment is hashed (sha256) so the same photo sent twice is stored once; webp is converted to png before upload; videos are linked/stored as received.
7. Outbound mails the Mail Engine sends (M1–M7)
ID — trigger	Body (English master; keep Hindi variant, auto-pick by detected language)
M1 — no identifying details found	Thank you for writing to DeoDap. We could not locate your order from this mail. Please reply with any one of these: registered order number, email ID, mobile number, AWB/tracking number — or any other detail registered with the order.
M2 — video/photo required (Route B)	Sorry to hear this. To register the complaint for order [ID], please reply with an unedited unboxing video AND a clear photo of the item — mandatory for damage / wrong / missing-item claims.
M3 — order# + phone missing (asked together, one mail)	To proceed, please share BOTH of these in one reply: (1) your order number, (2) the mobile number registered with the order.
M4 — auto-answer (Route A)	[Answer generated from playbook + live API data — status, EDD, tracking link, policy text, invoice attached, etc.] This mail closes the request; reply to reopen.
M5 — new ticket created	Your complaint is registered. Ticket number: [TKT-2026-NNNNNN]. Track status anytime: care.deodap.in/t?id=[hash]. Our team will update you on this same ticket.
M6 — ticket already open	A ticket for this issue is already open on your order: [TKT-2026-NNNNNN]. We have added today’s details to it. Track the latest update here: care.deodap.in/t?id=[hash].
M7 — reminder / auto-close on waiting states	Reminder at 24 h: “we’re waiting for [missing item] to proceed.” Auto-close at 72 h: “closing for now — reply anytime and it will reopen automatically.”

8. Status machine & dashboard
State (Mail Engine)	Meaning	Shows on dashboard as
new → classified	Ingested, extracted, classified.	—
ignored	Stopped at the ignore gate (spam / marketing / blocklist).	Blocked log
auto_resolved	Route A: answered & closed via API. No ticket.	Auto Handled
waiting_for_video	Route B: M2 sent, media pending.	Waiting For Evidence
awaiting_evidence	M1 or M3 sent — identifiers / mandatory fields pending.	Waiting For Evidence
awaiting_agent	Ticket created in Care Panel, or low-confidence draft assigned.	Awaiting Agent
escalated	Route D sensitive / high priority.	Awaiting Agent (priority)
in_progress → resolved → closed	Owned by the Care Panel from here; Mail Engine mirrors via webhook.	In Progress / Resolved
Pipeline on the dashboard: Waiting For Evidence → Awaiting Agent → In Progress → Resolved, surfaced as clickable KPI cards (pipeline_report). Timers: waiting states get a 24-hour reminder (M7) and auto-close at 72 hours; any reply within 7 days reopens the same case.
9. Edge rules & locked decisions
•	Blocklist is silent: addresses in the ignore section never get any reply and can never open a ticket.
•	Marketing gets no action: label + log only — never an auto-reply (avoids confirming the address to spammers).
•	One issue = one ticket: same order can hold multiple open tickets only if the issues are genuinely different.
•	Order# + phone always asked together in one mail — never two separate back-and-forth mails for two fields.
•	AWB extraction is AI-path only (no blind regex auto-action on AWBs) — it then verifies against ship.deodap.com before use.
•	Auto-resolved cases never create panel noise; they live in the Mail Engine log + dashboard counter only.
•	Language: reply in the customer’s detected language (EN/HI/GU) using template variants.
•	Open point to confirm: the agent-reply webhook (Section 6, row 4). Without it, agents must reply from the panel UI while the Mail Engine separately mails the customer — with it, one click in the panel triggers the customer mail through the Mail Engine. Recommended: build the webhook.
